4.3 Clearing Console Port Password via Passwordless startup.

Attention: After executing the passwordless startup through the simple command line, the password configuration in the configuration file is not deleted. If the device is restarted and re-entered, the original password is still required.

(1) After the device starts up, press "Ctrl+C" to enter Boot mode when prompted with the message "Press Ctrl+C to enter Boot Menu".

(2)  After entering Boot mode, press the "Ctrl+Q" key on the keyboard to enter the uboot simple command line, which will be displayed as "bootloader#".

(3) <main_config_password_clear> command is used to bypass password and start the device.

Press Ctrl+C to enter Boot Menu: 0

Entering simple UI....



====== BootLoader Menu("Ctrl+Z" to upper level) ======

TOP menu items.

************************************************

<T>0. Tftp utilities.</T>

XModem utilities.

2. Run main.

3. SetMac utilities.

4. Scattered utilities.

************************************************

Press a key to run the command:

bootloader# main_config_password_clear

……

Press RETURN to get started

(4) After entering the system, use the enable command to enter privileged mode. Delete the console interface password and then save the configuration.

Ruijie

Ruijie#config

Ruijie(config)#line console 0

Ruijie(config-line)#

Ruijie(config-line)#no login local

Ruijie(config-line)#no login

Ruijie(config-line)#no password

Ruijie(config-line)#end

